Findings: Lung volumes are low. Cardiac and mediastinal silhouette is stable. There has been interval removal of right internal jugular central venous catheter. No definite focal consolidation is seen. There is no large pleural effusion or pneumothorax. No overt pulmonary edema.
Impression: Low lung volumes without acute cardiopulmonary process.
